<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> have a thing about someone • have a thing with someone</xh5><p> <i>have a thing about someone</i>—(coll.) 1. feel a strong attraction to smb.: That smile, that jawline. No wonder Jacquie <u>had a thing about</u> him. 2. harbor a prejudice or fear about a person: Connie’s <u>got a “thing” about</u> police. “Never trust a policeman” is her motto.</p><p> <i>have a thing with someone</i>—(coll.) have a love affair with a person: “Are you sort of <u>having a thing with</u> Madalena?” “I’m interested in her,” he said. “But not sexually.”</p> </entry>
